    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-10T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="475"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/853b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-10T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 10, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>290. British Embassy has shown Department copy of telegram sent by British
                    Embassy Tehran to Foreign Office on March 1 concerning a message filed by the AP
                    representative in Tehran on the subject of the oil negotiations in Iran and copy
                    of Foreign Office reply of March 2. If this question is still alive, the
                    Department suggests that in addition to the British amendments, alteration be
                    made throughout the text to read “United States oil interests” or “companies”
                    instead of “United States Government” or any other wording which would make it
                    appear that negotiations are being carried on by this Government. It is further
                    believed wise to alter the penultimate sentence to avoid giving impression that
                    Prime Minister believes Iranians are negotiating with British and American
                    Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
